[node name="Label" type="RichTextLabel" parent="TerminalPage2/MarginContainer" unique_id=1889687064]
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_colors/default_color = Color(1, 0, 0, 1)
theme_override_fonts/normal_font = ExtResource("2_3ypq3")
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 14
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "<Translating...>
(Excerpt from Biological Records)

... Our kind, the Nexyr, have always been divided into classes. When we became a spacefairing civilisation, and stepped beyond the Jyrr system, with aid from the Masters technology, those classes have become our rankings. 

These classes, as follows, are ordered from lowest to highest, with a brief explanation of what they are and what they do.

1. Servant. Servant classes maintain lower level systems, such as waste, manufacturing, and low level computer work. Servants, unlike the superior rankings, cannot elevate their own ranking, but their children will be put through the trials of warriorhood, and have the opportunity to rise up.

2. Technician. Technicians operate the high level computer and technological infrastructure, and are trained in the expertise and knowledge needed to interface with the Masters technology. They can elevate their ranking, but are already held in high regard for their knowledge of our Masters technology.

3. Warrior and Voidtrooper. Warriors and Voidtroopers are considered the same rank, as they can interchange their roles at anytime. This class makes up the bulk of our military forces, especially Warriors.

4. Adepts. These are Warriors or Voidtroopers who have mastered their craft, and are sometimes granted shields for protection. The Adepts are often faster and stronger than their lesser counterparts, and have more tatical knowledge, allowing them to lead groups of lesser units.

5. Shipmaster. Shipmasters are the tatical geniuses that lead our fleets to victory against all who oppose us. Many shipmasters can operate a Vessel at once, but each Vessel has it's own Captain who leads the others. 

6. Fleetmaster / Grandmaster. One of the most prestigious roles in our society, the Fleetmaster leads a whole fleet, sometimes even multiple.

7. The Emperor of the Nexyr, and the High Court. The High Court and the Emperor still reside on Jyrr Prime, and await when we discover how to control the universe, like our masters once did.

(End of Excerpt)
<End of Terminal>"

