[node name="Label" type="RichTextLabel" parent="TerminalPage5/MarginContainer" unique_id=966158452]
layout_mode = 2
theme_override_colors/default_color = Color(0, 1, 0, 1)
theme_override_fonts/normal_font = ExtResource("2_3ypq3")
theme_override_font_sizes/normal_font_size = 14
bbcode_enabled = true
text = "<Incoming transmission from Pulsar...>

Well, well, well.

That fool just told me everything I need.

Oh no, Mr 'GrAnDMaSteR J'yMa' will melt me down. Sure.

Not once I take control of his ship and space his entire crew.

Hacking this ship's system was too easy, his will be no different.


Anyway. We have a lot more infomation, but still not a lot of time.

As I understand it, the Void Bringer, the \"Naaro Kora'thun\", and the Ancients 'Collapsing Fire' are all the same. 

The ancients and the masters are also the same. Evidently the ancients ruled or guided the Nexyr during the formation of their people, allowing them to become spacefairing much faster than humanity. 

The activity in the north is the Nexyr preparing the Void Bringer, to collapse Meridia's star, MIR - 49, as a trial and a show for their Emperor, who evidently has a much more powerful drive or was able to warp directly here instead of needed to traverse the stars to find the signals source, which will be why it took the fleets 30 years to get here. 

I detected over 4000 ships warp in a few moments ago, meaning the Nexyr are going to collapse the sun soon.

You must stop them, or they will be able to hold any species hostage with the Void Bringer, or worse.

Enter the teleporter in this room, and I'll teleport you to the Void Bringer in the north. 
You will have to find some way of destroying it or deactivating it permanently. I'll send down another toy for you to wipe out the very many hordes of aliens you will encounter.


<End transmission.>"

